{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b6b6f2bb-180c-4855-893f-4d761b47437d","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events API** in `MauiProgram.cs` (or your app builder setup):\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\nAdd `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.\n\nThis registers handlers via the `ILifecycleBuilder` — no need to subclass platform activities or app delegates. Each platform exposes its native events (e.g., `OnResume`, `WillTerminate`, etc.) through the same pattern.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"641ebd0e-38db-4fee-979f-3ec6da67cfb5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a code task.","outputTokens":291},"id":"61f9a35d-5266-456a-8334-93735075ffd1","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:44:43.837Z","parentId":"572a54fd-a92f-413e-814e-44f856dd6804"}
